# Blocks direct access to raw application source and build config, currently
# reachable only because Cloudflare Pages deploys the repository root as-is
# (no build step configured). Temporary mitigation — resolves permanently and
# automatically once Cloudflare is reconfigured to build from source and serve
# dist/ instead, which never contains these files under any build outcome.
# See docs/audit/FINAL_PRODUCTION_CERTIFICATION.md §8 / MASTER_PRODUCTION_CERTIFICATION.md.
#
# Scope is deliberately narrow: only paths directly confirmed exposed this
# engagement. Status 404 rewrites the response to "/" with a 404 status code —
# the real file's bytes are never sent back for a request matching these rules.
#
# The trailing "!" forces the rule even though a real file exists at each of
# these paths — Cloudflare Pages (like Netlify, whose _redirects syntax this
# follows) otherwise gives existing static files precedence over redirect
# rules, silently. Confirmed live: without "!", all six paths kept serving
# real file content after this file's first deploy (2026-07-20) — this is
# not a hypothetical, it's what the unforced version actually did in
# production.
/src/*               /  404!
/server.ts           /  404!
/vite.config.ts      /  404!
/tsconfig.json       /  404!
/package.json        /  404!
/package-lock.json   /  404!
